Tony &quot;Allstar&quot; Allison Strategy That is all of it. So here is some hints on the deck. <br>
Free People is the tricky part. When you pull weapons out you need to get them to certain people, Gimli should have these cards on him- Gimlis battle axe, hand axe, dwarven bracers, endurence of dwarves and gimlis helm. HE will be a 10 and only taking one wound if they get over him. Then there is Farin, I start him because it is more likly to be going against orcs of some kind. he will get a hand axe, dwarven axe, dwarven bracers and the endurance of dwarves. So then you are pretty much set to take on anything. Use your Dwarf guards as cannon fodder, never give them a weapon if someones is to big to handle even after the pump ups then let the guard have him. If you know that you will give up alot of twilight make sure you have a Flurry of blows in your hand or something to give him a boost, that is the deck weapons and pumps. Gloin and Fror are in case of Farin dying or the uruks showing their face. <br>
<br>
The Shadow side is rather easy. You have the armoried to get around that nasty archer stuff. The Ambitions and Bred for Battle help to pump up the minions unexpected. NOw you have to twilight nazguls so you can put a hurt on him try to assign bill with another minion or he is no good. Leave the Nazguls until sites 7,8,9 if you can that way there is no more sactuaries anywhere and everyone will exert at site 7, this will be easy if you use one minion or greed to kill off the lousy ranger they are playing. <br>
The Adventure path is very different compared to others with a uruk deck. <br>
